    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1006<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Navy Department</gloss> to the
                        Commander, United States Naval Forces in Europe</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SAHR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stark</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">routine</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18">18 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This is serial No. 33. <gloss target="#t_CominCh1">CominCh</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_CNO1">CNO</gloss> addressed <gloss target="#t_ComNavEu1"
                        >ComNavEu</gloss> for action and <gloss target="#t_ComNavForGer1"
                        >ComNavForGer</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> and directed
                        <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> to be forwarded <gloss
                        target="#t_CominCh1">CominCh</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CNO1"
                        >CNO</gloss>.<note n="1" xml:id="d1006fn1">Received by the United States
                        Delegation to the Berlin Conference on July 19 as a retransmission from the
                            <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Department.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Admiralty … [messages of July 7 and 11]<note n="2" xml:id="d1006fn2">Neither
                        printed.</note> indicate no US representation on <gloss
                        target="#t_Capcraft1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Capcraft</hi>
                    </gloss> Commission or provision for protecting US interest in disposing of
                    captured enemy small craft including tugs for immediate use in Pacific.</p>
                <p>There is an immediate and urgent need for seagoing tugs in carrying out approved
                    primary operations in the Pacific. Request you investigate and if desirable
                    arrange equal representation on <gloss target="#t_Capcraft1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Capcraft</hi>
                    </gloss> Commission or set up counter commission for US account in order to
                    secure all possible immediate assistance for Pacific seagoing tug requirements.
                    Suggest substitution of captured German tugs for US tugs now operating <gloss
                        target="#t_ETO1">ETO</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_WSA1">WSA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    Washington have been advised of Admiralty dispatches and feel their interest
                    identical with ours and that you and local <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    and <gloss target="#t_WSA1">WSA</gloss> representatives should handle to
                    satisfactory conclusion.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
